CONTEXT DelAtomCleanup IN ENGLISH
-- Negative test: orphan cleanup with DelAtom (the SURversion pattern). The rule
-- demands every Version to have a Document; a violating (orphan) Version is
-- removed with DelAtom. Deleting an atom is a negative write and the rule reads
-- `versionOf` (which the delete shrinks), so it is a non-monotone self-cycle.
-- But it only ever deletes: the population strictly shrinks and the loop
-- terminates by well-founded descent. This MUST stay silent (§6.5 refinement a).

RELATION versionOf[Version*Document] [UNI]

ROLE ExecEngine MAINTAINS "no orphan version"
RULE "no orphan version" : I[Version] |- versionOf;versionOf~
VIOLATION ( TXT "{EX} DelAtom;Version;", SRC I )

ENDCONTEXT
